<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-03-29T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-03-29T13:00:00-05:00" n="284" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d284">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.857M31</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-03-29T13:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">March 29, 1916, 1 p. m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2860. Department advised that liner <hi rend="italic">Manchester
                                    Engineer</hi> was torpedoed without warning off Waterford, March
                                27, with American citizens on board. Please inquire of the Foreign
                                Minister as to whether vessel was sunk by submarine belonging to
                                Germany or her allies. A prompt answer is expected.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>